Iavan Pijoos, News24Edenvale armed robbery. (YouTube) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Johannesburg - A man was shot and wounded during an armed robbery in Edenvale on Friday, police said. Six men in a silver car forced a white bakkie to stop on the R24 and robbed the three occupants of R40 000, Lieutenant Colonel Lungelo Dlamini said. The robbers stopped in front of the bakkie and opened fire, wounding the driver. In a video posted on Crime Air Network, the robbers can be heard firing five shots before they flee the scene. No arrests had yet been made.&nbsp;24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.